<sn><md>## French Guiana{.text-center}

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-lg-6
1. **Location**: French Guiana is located on the northeastern coast of South America, bordering Brazil to the south and east, and Suriname to the west.

2. **Territorial Status**: It is an overseas department and region of `France`, making it ++part of the European Union++.

3. **Capital**: The capital city is `Cayenne`, situated on the Atlantic coast.

6. **Climate**: The region has a **tropical rainforest climate**, with high humidity, heavy rainfall, and consistently warm temperatures throughout the year.

7. **Rivers**: Major rivers include the **Maroni River**, which forms the border with Suriname, and the **Oyapock River**, which borders Brazil.

&gt; **Spaceport**: The ++Guiana Space Centre++ near ==Kourou== is one of the world’s major spaceports, taking advantage of its proximity to the `equator for satellite launches`.

