:::</md></sn><sn><md>## Gyuana{.text-center}

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-lg-6

1. **Location**: Guyana is located on the northern coast of South America, bordered by **Venezuela** to the west, **Brazil** to the south, and **Suriname** to the east, with the **Atlantic Ocean** to the north.

2. **Capital**: The capital city is ==Georgetown==, situated on the Atlantic coast at the mouth of the Demerara River.

5. **Official Language**: The official language is ==English==, making Guyana unique as the only English-speaking country in South America.

6. **Climate**: The country has a **tropical climate**, with a hot, humid atmosphere and two rainy seasons (May–August and December–January).

7. **Rivers**: Guyana is known as the ==Land of Many Waters==, with major rivers including the **Essequibo**, **Demerara**, and **Berbice**.

9. **Topography**: The country features **coastal plains**, **hilly regions**, and **interior highlands**, including the famous **Kaieteur Falls**, one of the world’s tallest single-drop waterfalls.

&gt; **Unique Feature**: Guyana has vast `savannas in the south and west`, contrasting with the tropical rainforests, and is part of the **Guiana Shield**, one of the oldest geological formations on Earth.

